data.title: Lee Woods Obituary 2021

data.text:
WOODS, Lee Owen – Passes away peacefully with his wife by his side, on September 3, 2021, at his home in Utterson. He was in his 59th year. Beloved husband to Sherry Woods (nee Fisher) for 40 years. Cherished father of Crystal, and Tom Woods. Loving grandfather of Malcolm, Victoria, and William. Dear brother of Irene Beasley, Gwen Terry, William “Bill” Woods, Keith Woods (Lissa), Paul Woods, Mary Coutts (Perry). Brother-in-law of Jean (Randy), Debbie (Dale), Rose (Dave), Fred, Brenda, Linda (the late Dave), and the late Don. Proud friend of Tammy & Dwayne, and Wendy & Scott, Brad, Carol, and Suzanne & Paul. Son-in-law of Freida Fisher (the late Ted). Predeceased by his parents Bill and Aileen Woods. Lee will be deeply missed by uncle Carl and aunt Brenda, and his many other aunts and uncles, and by his cousins, nieces, nephews, great nieces, and great nephews.

Cremation has taken place and a Celebration of Life will be held at a later date.
